com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.model.implementation
Class Model

java.lang.Object
  com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.model.implementation.Model

public class Model
extends java.lang.Object

Represents an abstract heap state, consisting of ModelVariable instances together with associated ModelInstance instances. See separate documentation for both.

christopher

EMPTY_MODEL

public static final Model EMPTY_MODEL

buffer

private final java.util.HashMap<ModelVariable,ModelVariable> buffer
Buffers variables which currently cannot be inserted due to broken reference dependencies. Primarily, this will occur when the user tries to insert a variable as a field into an instace which currently does'nt exist. This can happens if this class is used in non-postorder visitations of Term ASTs. Use mainly to allow safe visitations.

add

public void add(ModelVariable variable,
                java.lang.Object instance)
Adds a variable to the heap, causing it to point to a given object instance. If the variable already exists on the heap, this method will cause the variable to point to the new instance instead, unless the variable is declared as final.

Parameters:
variable - the variable to be added
instance - the instance the variable will point to. Can be null.

assignPointer

public void assignPointer(ModelVariable target,
                          ModelVariable other)
Links two ModelVariable instances, causing target to point to the ModelInstance which other is pointing to.

Parameters:
target - the target variable, i.e. the one the address of the instance is being bound to. Cannot be null
other - the other variable, i.e. the one currently holding the address of the instance. Cannot be null
